{
  "stem": "26111.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I must go back to the testimony of an uncle of mine, a relative who was grown-up at-- in the '20s, and who, many years later, I had some long conversations with when he was-- worked for the Israeli government, living for a long time already in Israel.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was their chief negotiator with the German government in Bonn on the compensation question and working all those things out with them.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we had dinner.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was living in Switzerland at the time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This was in the early '70s or late '60s.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And, and I got an eye-opener about assimilation, about this very question that Jews had, had to fight very hard for, for assimilation, for becoming citizens, for equality.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They never got equality.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They did get citizenship in the-- in the 1900s.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But there was always discrimination.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it was more or less accepted.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Besides, usually the arts, even the professions, to some extent, were the people where you-- were the-- were the areas where you found the more enlightened or the less unenlightened people in-- than, than in, for example, the bureaucratic class or the, the [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] other, other different economic classes, which were not as well-educated, and therefore, were far more willing to follow people like Hitler later on.",
      "word_count": 70
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They couldn't change their name, for example.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, they could change their name if they wish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The, the-- they weren't admitted to many professions.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Not generally known that in, in Germany before the beginning of the 19th century, no Jew was able to have a, a shop.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Only they were able to be itinerant traders with their shop.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Their shop was the tray of their goods that they carried in front of them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This was outside the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
